        "print(\"\"\"\n",
        "Section 2 - Signal Preprocessing: Filtering Out Noise\n",
        "======================================================================\n",
        "\n",
        "Raw ECG signals contain noise that has nothing to do with heart activity:\n",
        "- Baseline wander (slow drift from patient breathing/movement)\n",
        "- Powerline interference (60 Hz electrical noise)\n",
        "- High-frequency muscle artifact\n",
        "\n",
        "We apply a bandpass filter (0.5-40 Hz) to isolate the frequency range where\n",
        "genuine cardiac electrical activity lives, which is standard practice in\n",
        "ECG signal processing.\n",
        "\"\"\")"
      ],
