            "Each segmented heartbeat is converted into a set of numerical features that\n",
            "capture its shape and timing characteristics — the same kind of features a\n",
            "cardiologist implicitly evaluates when reading an ECG strip:\n",
            "\n",
            "- Statistical shape features (mean, std, skewness, kurtosis of the waveform)\n",
            "- Peak amplitude and signal energy\n",
            "- RR interval context (time since the previous beat, since arrhythmias often\n",
            "  disrupt normal heart rhythm timing)\n",
            "\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
