        "Summary\n",
        "======================================================================\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook builds an end-to-end biomedical signal processing pipeline: it\n",
        "downloads real ECG recordings and cardiologist annotations from PhysioNet's\n",
        "MIT-BIH Arrhythmia Database, applies bandpass filtering to remove physiological\n",
        "and electrical noise, segments individual heartbeats, extracts clinically\n",
        "relevant time-domain features, and trains a Random Forest classifier to detect\n",
        "arrhythmias. Evaluation focuses on per-class sensitivity rather than overall\n",
        "accuracy, since missing a dangerous arrhythmia (like a PVC) is far costlier\n",
        "than a false alarm. Patient-level train/test splitting avoids data leakage.\n",
        "\n",
        "Limitations: MIT-BIH is a small, decades-old dataset from a limited patient\n",
        "population at one hospital. A real clinical deployment would require larger,\n",
        "more diverse, and more recent data, prospective validation, and regulatory\n",
        "clearance (FDA 510(k) or De Novo pathway) before any clinical use.\n",
        "\n",
